| Step | Action                                 | Location                                    |
| ---- | -------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| 1️⃣  | Frontend connects & requests init data | `socket.emit("request:init")`               |
| 2️⃣  | Backend sends users & message history  | `socket.emit("user:list")` & `chat:history` |
| 3️⃣  | Frontend shows user list & messages    | `setUsers()` / `setMessages()`              |
| 4️⃣  | User sends a message                   | `socket.emit("chat:message")`               |
| 5️⃣  | Backend saves message & broadcasts it  | `insertMessage.run(...)` + `io.emit(...)`   |
| 6️⃣  | Frontend receives it & updates UI      | `socket.on("chat:message")`                 |


| Situation                          | Are plugins/routes needed? |
| ---------------------------------- | -------------------------- |
| Only using Socket.IO               | ❌ Not needed               |
| Only one or two simple HTTP routes | ❌ Not needed               |
| Not reusing logic across files     | ❌ Not needed               |
| No need for auth/middleware hooks  | ❌ Not needed               |
